A large lithography fine art print by Hilly van Eerten with some archetype human figures, she made frequently in the period 1993 - 1995
This lithography print is print No. 3 of 6

period: 1992 - 1996: lithography fine art prints, with archetypal figures & forms
serie: lithography art prints with figures & forms from gravestones
description:
Three human figures are the subject of this lithography fine art print, made by Dutch graphic artist Hilly van Eerten in 1995.
This print is No. 3 of 5.

period: 1992 - 1996: lithography fine art prints, with archetypal figures & forms
serie: lithography art prints with figures & forms from gravestones
description:
Three human and archaic figures, placed in a green surrounding area - lithography fine print art 1995 by graphic artist Hilly van Eerten

title: 'Departure of three Figures' - lithography fine print art, 1996; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1992 - 1996: lithography fine art prints, with archetypal figures & forms
serie: lithography art prints with figures & forms from gravestones
description:
This lithography fine art print was the last print Hilly van Eerten made with the subject of human archetype figures on gravestones and tombstones; she frequently made from 1993 till 1996 in Amsterdam. 
This art print is No 3. of 6.

title: Two Figures in a place' - lithography fine print art, 1996; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1992 - 1996: lithography fine art prints, with archetypal figures & forms
serie: lithography art prints with figures & forms from gravestones
description:
Lithography print of archetype human figures, taken from existing gravestones around Amsterdam city, The Netherlands. 
graphic artist Hilly van Eerten used here photos she made of gravestones in Berlin and Prague, circa 1993.
This print is No. 8 of 8.

title: 'The Jewish cemetery' - lithography fine print art, 1996; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1992 - 1996: lithography fine art prints, with archetypal figures & forms
serie: lithography art prints with figures & forms from gravestones
description:
Subject of this lithography fine art print were several figures on gravestones at the Jewish Cemetery in Prague, Hilly van Eerten visited that time.
The gravestones there she saw criss-cross spread, what she liked to express in this lithography art print. 
Print No. 9 of 10

title: 'Gate and Window' - lithography print art, 1996; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1992 - 1996: lithography fine art prints, with archetypal figures & forms
serie: lithography art prints with figures & forms from gravestones
description:
Black-white lithography fine art print of a gravestone; the gravestone is reconstructed by Hilly van Eerten with a hole to break the solid form of the stone.
Print No 2. of 11

title: 'Toppled Gravestones' - lithography fine print art, 1996; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1992 - 1996: lithography fine art prints, with archetypal figures & forms
serie: lithography art prints with figures & forms from gravestones
description:
Lithography print No. 6 of 8.
Impression of toppled gravestones by Dutch graphic artist Hilly van Eerten, 1996

title: 'Still-life of Food' - lithography fine print art, 1997; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: lithography art prints with food as subject
description:
The inspiration of this lithography art print  were some watercolor sketches Hilly van Eerten painted of food: a herring with onions, three tomatoes and one leek, all on a plate.
It was done in the context of a exposition and a collective graphic art-print map with five other graphic artists, at the Grafisch Atelier in Amsterdam.
Print No. 13 of 25.

title: 'Koh Chang 1.' - lithography fine print art, 1997; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: lithography fine art prints after photos of Koh Chang, Thailand
description:
title: Koh Chang 1.
Hilly van Eerten made this lithography art print after her photos she made during a stay in 1996 in Thailand, on the island Koh Chang.
This printed image is a collage-mixture of impressions: sea, trees, mountains and the landscape in Thailand. 
Print No. 9 of 10

title: 'The gate again' - lithography print art, 1997; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
description:
a lithography fine art print, cut out along its outer form and glued on another paper.
This art-print is made in relation to Hilly van Eerten's photos of gravestones - but by accident two times made in the analog camera, what resulted in a completely other image.
Print No 5. of 10.

title: 'Fish and a Drink' - lithography print art, 1998; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: lithography art prints with food as subject
description:
This small lithography art print was made for an anniversary calendar, made in the context of the 40th anniversary of the Amsterdams Grafisch Atelier, where Hilly van Eerten frequently printed her graphic print art. 
This print is No 4 of a series of 10 E.A..

title: 'Koh Chang & triangle' - lithography printing art,1998; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: lithography fine art prints after photos of Koh Chang, Thailand
description:
This lithography fine art print was printed on rice-paper and afterwards glued on thicker paper.
Hilly van Eerten used her photos of the sea in Thailand, near the island Koh Chang, combined with a subtle triangle.
print No. 2 of 11.

title: 'Koh Chang 3.' - lithography fine print art, 1998; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: lithography fine art prints after photos of Koh Chang, Thailand
description:
This lithography fine print art is printed in different color-layers.
Hilly van Eerten combined  several images of her photos - impressions of the sea in Thailand near the island Koh Chang.
Print No 7. of 7

title: 'no title' - lithography fine print art,1998; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
description:
no title, subject unknown.
Lithography art print by Dutch graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
print No. 7 of 10.

title: 'Three tombstones in red', 7/12 -  lithography fine print art; 1999; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: lithography art prints with figures & forms from gravestones
description:
A lithography print made of photos of tombstones which the artist took at the Jewish graveyard in Prague.
Made by Dutch graphic woman-artist Hilly van Eerten.

title: 'Eye upon Gate'  - photo-collage, 2000; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
description:
A photo-collage made from pictures which Hilly van Eerten took in New York in 1999. 
Upper picture is from an artwork in the Brooklyn Museum. 
Belowr: picture of a gate in Manhattan.

title: 'New York 2.' - lithography art print of New York Manhattan, 2000; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
description:
This lithography print is made from impressions of New York Manhattan, visited earlier by graphic Dutch artist Hilly van Eerten.
She first copied one photo on paper; then several lithography layers were printed over the black-white copy. 
Print No. 3 of 8.

title: 'The Twelve Gates' - mono-print art, 2001; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 2000 - 2002: mono-type art print with subject Gates
serie: Gates - in mono-type art print, 2001-2002
description:
This mono-type print is one of the earliest mono-types that Hilly van Eerten made ever.
This print she created from her photo of the concentration-camp Theresienstadt, near Prague, she visited in 1991.
One of the gates there she uses in this art print by repeating the same profile of the gate on her photo.

title: 'In front of & behind The Gates' No 2. - mono-print art; graphic artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 2000 - 2002: mono-type art print with subject Gates
serie: Gates - in mono-type art print, 2001-2002
description:
A mono-print, made from photos by of gates in New York City, Manhattan.
One detail of the gate is used here repeatedly in this monoprint art.
This print is started with yellow as subsurface. Afterwards the red text was printed, followed by printing the cut pieces of the gate-form. 
This art-print is an unique original print, as all the mono-types of Hilly van Eerten are - because she looses the basic-images during the print-process.

title: 'Fishing Nets' No 2. - graphic art-print, 2003; artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: Fishing nets - in monoprint; 2003-2004
description: This mono-type print was made after pictures of the fishing nets, Hilly van Eerten made in the Dutch harbor of IJmuiden, circa 2001.

title: 'Red & Green fishnets', mixed media, 2003; artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: Fishing nets - in monoprint; 2003-2004
description:
This mixed media art-work is created by Hilly van Eerten, first in mono-type print and afterwards drawn in oil-pastel.
The print was glued on a bigger paper before she used the oil sticks.

title: 'Fishing nets' No 3.  - graphic print art, 2004; artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: Fishing nets - in monoprint; 2003-2004
description:
This work is a combination of photography and drawing; both used as source-material to print this unique mono-type.
The pictures of the fishing nets  Hilly van Eerten took in the Dutch harbor of IJmuiden, circa 2001.
This illustrates the way she works - using the collected images from her own photography as the basis for making her unique fine art prints.

title: 'Roof tiles' No 6. - graphic print art, 2005; artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: Roof tiles - in mono-type print; 2005
description: This unique mono-type is partly made after photos of roof tiles, made at the island Gran Canaria where the living houses had typical round tiles on their roofs.

title: 'Roof tiles' No 7 - graphic print art, 2005; artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: Roof tiles - in mono-type print; 2005
description: This unique mono-type is made after photos of roof tiles, made at the island Gran Canaria where the living houses had typical round tiles on their roofs.

title: 'Blue Cobblestones' No 1. - mono-print fine art; artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: Paving stones - in mono-type print; 2006
description:
title: Blue Cobblestones No 1.
This unique mono-type fine art print is made from photos of the artist she made  in the old city Maastricht, a city with original medieval cobblestones.. 
Only one print was made; so an unique print because the technique is mono-print!.
Made by Dutch graphic woman-artist Hilly van Eerten.

title: 'Flee-market near Daniel Meijer square, Amsterdam', - mono-print, 2006; Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: Modern Cities - in mono-type print; from 2007
description:
One of the first mono-prints of Hilly van Eerten, made from her photos with an urban subject / focus - as source.
Here pictures are used of the square in front of the Portuguese Jewish synagogue in Amsterdam city.

title: 'Pavement - red Cobble-stones & White color' - mono-print art, 2006; artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: Paving stones - in mono-type print; 2006
description: A mono-type made from several pictures Hilly van Eerten made of the cobble-stone pavement in the old city-center of Maastricht in 2005.

title: 'Pavement - Red and Black Cobble-stones', - mono-print, 2006; artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: Paving stones - in mono-type print; 2006
description: A mono-type made from two different pictures Hilly van Eerten made of the cobble-stone pavement in the Dutch old city-center of Maastricht in 2005.

title: 'Daniel Meyerplein' No 6. - mono-print, 2007; artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 2007 - 2015: mono-print art, from her photos of Dutch cities
serie: Modern Cities - in mono-type print; from 2007
description: Mono-type from photos of the Daniel Meyer square in Amsterdam city, combined with her photos of texts from Bali Indonesia: collage

title: 'Cobble-stones, mixed' - mono-print collage, 2007; artist Hilly van Eerten
period: 2007 - 2015: mono-print art, from her photos of Dutch cities
serie: Paving stones - in mono-type print; 2006
description:
A printed collage of several pictures like the cobble-stone pavement of the city Maastricht and the Daniel Meyer square in Amsterdam city.
This art print is destroyed by the artist, because of damage of the paper.

title: 'New Public Library of Amsterdam' No 2. - mono-print-art, 2009; artist Hilly van eerten
period: 1996 - 2000: lithography fine art prints with diverse subjects
serie: Modern Cities - in mono-type print; from 2007
description: A mono-type , made out of her photos of the building-activities at the area Oosterdok in Amsterdam city. mixed and combined with images of new high architecture from Rotterdam. Collage of images!

title: 'Modern City' No 1. - mono-print art, 2010; Dutch artist, Hilly van Eerten
period: 2007 - 2015: mono-print art, from her photos of Dutch cities
serie: Building cranes - in mono-type print; from 2010
description:
This mono-type is a combination of several images, taken from her pictures.
One image comes from the water towers on the roofs in Manhattan.
The images of the building cranes are from photos - taken in Dutch big cities The Hague, Rotterdam and Amsterdam.

period: 2007 - 2015: mono-print art, from her photos of Dutch cities
serie: Building cranes - in mono-type print; from 2010
description:
This mono-type art print is a combination of several images, taken from her pictures.
One image comes from the water towers on the roofs in Manhattan.
The images of the building cranes are from her photos she made in Dutch big cities The Hague, Rotterdam and Amsterdam.

title: 'Gray building crane and watertowers in Manhattan' - mono-print art, 2010; Dutch artist, Hilly van Eerten
period: 2007 - 2015: mono-print art, from her photos of Dutch cities
serie: Building cranes - in mono-type print; from 2010
description:
This mono-type art print is a combination of several images.
One image comes from the water towers on the roofs in Manhattan, New York City.
The images of the building cranes are from her photos she made in the  Dutch big cities Rotterdam and Amsterdam.

title: 'New York City with Water Towers' No 1. - mono-print art, 2010; Dutch artist, Hilly van Eerten
period: 2007 - 2015: mono-print art, from her photos of Dutch cities
serie: Building cranes - in mono-type print; from 2010

This mono-type art print is a combination of several images, taken from her pictures.
One image comes from the water towers on the roofs in Manhattan.
Another image shows the fronts of residential blocks in Manhattan, New York City.
